{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/kube-rs/kube/pulls/360", "id": 545674538, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NTQ1Njc0NTM4", "html_url": "https://github.com/kube-rs/kube/pull/360", "diff_url": "https://github.com/kube-rs/kube/pull/360.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/kube-rs/kube/pull/360.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/kube-rs/kube/issues/360", "number": 360, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "Add WebSocket connection support and implement `/attach` and `/exec`", "user": {"login": "kazk", "id": 639336, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjYzOTMzNg==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/639336?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kazk", "html_url": "https://github.com/kazk", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kazk/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kazk/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kazk/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kazk/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kazk/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kazk/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kazk/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kazk/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kazk/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "Attempt to support WebSocket connection. \r\n\r\n@clux \r\n\r\nI'd like to know if this is on the right track before spending more time on it. ~~I _think_ it works, but haven't tried.~~ (outputting to stdout works, see `pod_attach` example)\r\nThis is based on https://github.com/clux/kube-rs/issues/229#issuecomment-751234315\r\n\r\nI had to change `Config` a bit so that it's less coupled with `reqwest` to create `AsyncTlsConnector` for WebSocket connection when creating a `Client`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n- [x] Support WebSocket connection\r\n    - [x] `native-tls`\r\n    - [x] `rustls` (`accept_invalid_certs` not supported at the moment, need `rustls` 0.17.0+ and that requires updating `tokio` first)\r\n- [x] Make WebSocket opt-in with `ws` feature\r\n- [x] Decide how to implement `attach`/`exec` methods.\r\n    - Added `AttachedProcess` struct. Need review/feedback.\r\n- [x] Add `/attach` (see `pod_attach` example)\r\n- [x] Add `/exec` (see `pod_exec` example)\r\n- [x] Move most of `ws` specific code into a separate module. This should make it much easier to maintain.\r\n- [x] Validate params. We only get 400 status error without any information when making connection :(\r\n    - [At least one of `stdin`, `stdout`, `stderr` must be set](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/80be1d6c7217b99fb6ff083a190b44af53a628fc/pkg/kubelet/cri/streaming/server.go#L173-L175)\r\n    - [`stderr` and `tty` cannot be both set because multiplexing is not supported](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/80be1d6c7217b99fb6ff083a190b44af53a628fc/pkg/kubelet/cri/streaming/server.go#L168-L172). `stderr` will be ignored.\r\n- [x] ~~Make [`WebSocketConfig`](https://docs.rs/tungstenite/0.11.1/tungstenite/protocol/struct.WebSocketConfig.html) configurable.~~ Will do when there's a need.\r\n- [x] Make the sizes of internal buffers configurable\r\n- [x] Rename `api/streaming` to `api/remote_command`\r\n- [x] Improve documentation for `AttachParams`\r\n    - Explain how `stdin`, `stdout`, `stderr` allows access to writer/streams from `AttachedProcess`\r\n- [x] Improve documentation for `AttachedProcess`\r\n    - Explain how `stdin()`, `stdout()`, `stderr()` works", "created_at": "2020-12-26T09:16:15Z", "updated_at": "2021-01-02T17:55:03Z", "closed_at": "2021-01-02T12:19:45Z", "merged_at": "2021-01-02T12:19:45Z", "merge_commit_sha": "b8cf11fabdb5643cbcc676c61cc618f8eef483d5", "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [{"login": "nightkr", "id": 649832, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY0OTgzMg==", "avatar_url": "https://avata